metadata.name: CrossWorlds #303
metadata.description:
In 2057 an error occurred in the particle accelerator machine causing a diversion in space-time that leads to duplication of our world. Scientists discovered that they can travel to these "CrossWorlds" with wormholes plagued by singularities occurring at weakened points of the fabric between worlds. In time, some worlds became hostile to each other, tried to plunder their natural resources, and take over civilizations but other worlds learned how to co-exist peacefully...
------------------
Animation_
Press R: Rotates the world 180Â°
Idle: Default animation cycles from corner to corner
Mouse: Cursor-dependent animation
MobileDevice: Controls the animation with the orientation of the device. (Android only)
------------------
Live-view_
Resolution: Add "&res=" end of your url with a resolution multiplier. (0.5-6)
Press S: Saves the current scene (Default 1600x1600 px).
Press L: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as PNG.
Press D: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as SVG.
------------------
Created with p5js.

metadata.name: Finestre #337
metadata.description:
"Finestre" means windows or apertures in Italian. This generative art project was inspired by the appreciation of collected memories, windows in time to our past experiences and loved ones. Using basic geometry such as rectangles, squares, circles, ellipses, triangles with random compositions and many possible color palettes, Finestre presents our impression of portals to the Universes of collected memories through abstract still code-based outputs.

Finestre is a collaboration generative art project between generative artists Gonz0x and Schizzo.

Finestre has some fun interactive features which allows collectors to view the work in different configurations. For example, collectors can isolate the deconstructed background layers, isolate the main constructed layer, add Grain and also enter a Free Play mode which allows for the option to draw background and foreground layers, stacking infinitely. You can Save off a render as a .png.

Press "C" for Constructed Mode (Isolate Foreground)
Press "D" for Deconstructed Mode (Isolate Background)
Press "R" to reset to Default = C & D
Press "G" to add grain texture with each press
Press "S" saves render
 
Press "F" to toggle Free Play mode
In Free Play, Press "Q" repeatedly to add Deconstructed layers
In Free Play, Press "W" repeatedly to add Constructed layers

metadata.name: Reverberations #43
metadata.description:
[ CLICK TO START THE SOUND ]
Best viewed on a decent GPU for 60fps rendering
Play the instrument by clicking or touching the blobs
Supports any aspect ratio, however the resulting simulation will vary!

Everything in the universe is made up of vibrating energy, including us. Our thoughts and emotions are also vibrations of energy that influence the frequencies around us. 
Be kind.

Controls
[ click / touch ] - split blobs
[ /?play ] - query string to avoid automatic splits
[ s ] - save image
[ f ] - full screen

Created with Three.js + Rapier.js + Tone.js

metadata.description:
The Oneiroi(Gods of Dreams), by NJT

The Oneiroi is inspired by Roman ancient Gods which ia a unique digital-hand-drawing that can Randomly Generate.

The Oneiroi collection contains Traits 26 (141 layers), and it can make your own unique NFT.

These NFTs are randomly minted, which is a chance for everyone to get a rare version.


Don't hesitate to send me DM on twitter for more info : @mahdi_njt

metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #263
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Rules are selected randomly among a pre-selection of 53 rules from which nice behaviors emerge.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.
